  "text": "A graft composite was passed through the tibial and femoral tunnels, taking care to prevent damage to the remnant ( Figure 1 and Video 2). The graft was then inserted into the knee joint through an anteromedial portal and was secured to the lateral femoral cortex by flipping the Telos Button (Ai-Mdic), introduced through a 1-cm incision on the lateral thigh at the femur side. [CITATION_1] The double-stapling technique [CITATION_2] was used for graft fixation on the tibial side at 30 of knee flexion.",
